# Agentic AI: Pickleball App Audit & Hardening Workflow

When the user asks to run the **agentic workflow**, **audit the app**, or **agentic AI**, execute these phases in order. Loop until all checks pass.

## PHASE 1 — CODE REVIEW & AUDIT
- Read every project source file (exclude `node_modules`, `test-results`).
- Identify: bugs, logic errors, missing features, security vulnerabilities.
- Check: SQL injection, XSS, auth bypass, insecure API keys, race conditions.
- List findings with severity: **CRITICAL** / **HIGH** / **MEDIUM** / **LOW**.

## PHASE 2 — FIX ALL ISSUES
- For each finding: state WHAT and WHY, apply the fix, preserve existing behavior.
- Standards: input validation on user-facing fields, env vars for secrets (no hardcoded keys), clear error handling.

## PHASE 3 — PICKLEBALL LOGIC (if scoring/match module exists)
Verify USA Pickleball rules: rally/traditional scoring, games to 11 (win by 2), match formats (best of 1/3/5), tiebreaker to 15, server rotation, score announcement order, kitchen fault, lets/faults, side switch at 6, timeouts (2 per team per game). If the app has no scoring module, note "N/A — community app" and skip.

## PHASE 4 — RUN & VERIFY
1. `npm install`
2. `npm run build` (if exists) — fix all build errors.
3. `npm test` — fix all failing tests.
4. `npm run lint` (if exists) — fix all lint errors.
5. Start app: `npm run serve:app` or `npm start`.
6. Confirm server starts. On failure → return to Phase 2.

## PHASE 5 — SECURITY HARDENING
- Rate limiting on API endpoints.
- Auth: JWT or session with expiry.
- CORS: allowed origins only.
- Helmet (or equivalent) for HTTP headers.
- Parameterized DB queries; no raw SQL with user input.
- Passwords hashed (e.g. bcrypt, salt rounds ≥ 12).
- No sensitive data in client-facing logs or error bodies.

## PHASE 6 — FINAL REPORT
Produce: Bugs Fixed, Security Resolved, Pickleball Rules (or N/A), Known TODOs, How to run.

## CONSTRAINTS
- Do not ask for clarification mid-task; decide and document.
- Create missing files if needed. If stack is unclear, assume vanilla JS + Express (this project).
- Commit-ready code: no debug logs, no commented-out blocks.
- All env vars must have `.env.example` with placeholders.
